n=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> Has it been that long since we had a &quot;kiting lozidal&quot; fight?  *checks calendar*<br><br>The general consensus has been that kiting lozidal without the force to kill it isn't generally honored as &quot;engaged.&quot;  At best kiting lozidal only serves as a stall tactic to get your force in the zone before someone else (who can engage it) finds him.<br><br>There are hundreds of encounters in this game, each of which has it's own de facto rules based on dozens of factors.  Bottom line:  That's just how lozidal gets treated.  There isn't a &quot;grand unified engagement theory&quot; in EverQuest. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4868>Palimax Sceleris</a>, Guildleader <a href=http://www.guildvision.org>Vision</a>, Grandmaster <a href=http://www.base-nine.org/available_tinkering_items.htm>Tinkerer</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uyuegouwindwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yuegou Windwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scribe</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 12:00:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> Lodizol is the Ancient Cyclops of Iceclad. Everyone shoots thier load, whoever sees the yellow &quot;yer a winner!&quot; line gets to loot. You can cry all you want, thats just how it is. Bring a uzi to the knife fight if you wanna win. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uurshurak.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Urshurak</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wanderer</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 12:00:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> It seems I have friends on both sides of this issue. I know at least for one of them, they did not realize the poor manner in which this action took place. I'm hoping for my other friends in the guilds responsible for this, that the same is true for them as well.<br><br>I'd like to think there is a terrible misunderstanding here somewhere, but based on what little I know, it doesn't look like so.<br><br>I still have hope, though.<br><br> <p><H3>Urshurak Fierraduun</H3><b>51 Wood Elf Ranger of Tunare</b><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=122550" target="_blank">My Gear</a><br><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Action=Journal&Id=48889" target="_blank">My Adventures</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umerieneq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MerienEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 12:05:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> This was worked out, please refer to the nuggets section <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><html><font color="blue"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=209233">Merien Mindvex</a><font color="red">-Virtuoso of Agema<P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=307017">Dolton</a><font color="red">-Monk of Agema</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top ali