lor=#ff0000>(8/2/02 4:29:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> This was not the case Saeeliel...<br><br>We did have the power in the zone to take care of him as did the other guild, and when our monk pulled him to us, we were on him first. However, as many Lodi fights go when this is the case, the other guild decided to jump on him also...<br><br>All things aside, this issue has been resolved in a civilized manner unlike many of the lengthy &quot;Omg this person KSed me&quot; type posts and is no longer open for discussion. <p><html><font color="blue"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=209233">Merien Mindvex</a><font color="red">-Virtuoso of Agema<P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=307017">Dolton</a><font color="red">-Monk of Agema</html></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umandari.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mandari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 4:55:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.nc.rr.com/prismites/icon1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> For the record, when we pulled him they only had a couple people in zone. I suspect both guild's forces zoned in at approximately the same time, but our 17 easily outmatched their 7 and we got the kill.  Had I known they had enough on scene I'd not bother to leave my xp camp to watch the turtle die.  I don't care to run over anyone for a few pixels.  I didn't share loot because I thought we KS'd -- we made a fair engagement -- I shared the loot because I'd rather make friends than enemies. Other than Danaldor crying to the zone, it was settled quite amicably.  Thread over.<br> <p>Thormir Anvilheart<br>Oracle<br>Leader of <A HREF="http://home.nc.rr.com/prismites">PRISM</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uswifft.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Swifft</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 6:04:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> I have yet to hear Bada's description of how it all went. I was the officer of agema on hand and he was dealing with the situation quite nicely. Dispite a few ramblings from a few members of Agema I felt the rest handled themselves nicely.<br>Situation resolved far as i am concerned.<br><br><br>-Crashem Berygud 60th Warlord<br>    Officer and MT of Agema <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb.html" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/01/11/09/flamingtext_com.143519193.jpg" border=0 alt="Image by FlamingText.com"></a><br>Image by <a href="http://www.flamingtext.com/ezb2.html">FlamingText.com</a></BODY></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrist0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crist0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 7:13:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> Lodi is soloable...<br><br>Technically 1 person could be &quot;sufficient force&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucrydeeossiriand.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Crydee Ossiriand</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Autosig Tracker</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 7:49:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://questing-ranger.com/images/mboards/archer-2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> I once kited Lodizal around Iceclad Ocean for a long time while waiting for the one guild wizard that was on to finish what he was quad-kiting and get around to picking people up... This was with another guild present in the zone who were nice enough to honour me outmaneuvering them and getting to the turtle first.<br><br>On another occasion though, the opposing guild didn't like being beaten to Lodizal and started nuking him so that he'd summon me. It didn't matter that we actually had sufficiant force in the zone to begin with and more arriving as the turtle was being pulled.<br><br><br>When it gets down to it, you cannot really expect or depend on anything when camping Lodizal other than that someone is going to kill the turtle within a minute of him spawning.<br> <p><A HREF="http://www.questing-ranger.com" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://www.questing-ranger.com/images/mboards/signature.jpg" WIDTH="468" HEIGHT="98"></A><BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=136038" TARGET="_blank">View Magelo Profile</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ubadaayonae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bada Ayonae</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 9:16:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Ok -- basically what happened is I sat ontop of Lodizal's spawn point most of Thursday. He spawns and I begin to kite him around while our forces gather. <br><br>While our forces are gathering I notice Kelraz of Prism following me and the turtle around. <br><br>Agema and Prism members begin to pour into the zone at approximately the same time. They had 2 groups, we had 1. <br><br>I asked Kelraz to back off as I had already engaged the turtle and I was told he didn't care if we engaged it and that Prism was taking it (/rude).<br><br>Basically after this it became a FFA - everyone beating on the turtle to get the kill. Prism gets the kill (they had 2x as many people inzone as Agema). <br><br>I discussed it with Thormir and they agreed to split the loot (I felt this was the best decision to make at this point -- we take something or get nothing). <br><br><br>Thormir I have to say I was pleasantly suprised dealing with you yesterday however I also would like to add that Kelraz in my opinion did something that was uncalled for and quite honestly just outside /rude. <br><br>I was told today in guildchat that we have had good relations with you in the past (a recent Dragon Necropolis wipeout for Prism comes to mind -- where Agema rezsticked your entire guild). You might want to keep a closer eye on some of your members -- what goes around comes around in life and it sure seems to apply to EverQuest aswell. <br><br>As far as comments/duels made by Danaldor to members of prism I am sorry that it happened but I can also very easily understand his anger -- I was quite upset myself aswell.<br><br>In any case I hope this does not happen again and look forward to good relations with Prism in the future.<br><br>Bada Bing <br>Agema  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uxaeviouran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xaeviouran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 9:43:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: turtle turtle</span><hr size=1> Interesting discussion started on Lozi.......I always respect a camp myself..I'm old school EQ before the Play nice rules or whatever.  However...my understanding is that Lozi is one of those spawns that GM's wont' respond about.  Basically first guidl to kill it..wins.  totally FFA.  Am I correct in this?  Not that I would jump on someone and try to steal it...I&quot;m just curious if my understanding of how VI views the spawn is accurate.   I hope this post made sense I&quot;m quite tired.<br><br>Xaeviouran Orionne<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ufelicia2k.showPublicProfile?language=EN>felicia2k</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(8/2/02 10:46:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1804.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ..</span><hr size=1> A sham